Morgan Stanley May Sell Shanghai Motel Management, WSJ Says

-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 
2011-02-23T14:55:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/morgan-stanley-may-sell-shanghai-motel-management-wsj-says.html
  Morgan Stanley  may sell the Shanghai
Motel Management Co. for as much as $1 billion, the Wall Street
Journal reported on its website, citing unidentified people
familiar with the matter.  Shanghai Motel Management operates a chain under the Motel
168 brand. Morgan Stanely bought 20 percent of the company in
2006 for $20 million, the Journal reported. Morgan Stanley now
controls 59 percent of the company, the Journal said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  